Chuck,<br>
 <br>
Sometime ago I started to look for lost buddies, advertized in Vietnam Magazine and received some calls from Marines that served in the same area I did but were from different units. You might want to try to do the same.<br><br>
If you can find out what Division, battalion, regiment, or company he served with that would help a lot. If you find that information I might be able to place you in contact with Marines that served in that unit, around that same time. Marines at that time had gone there as a unit, but we started rotating after that and some units changed same to prevent the whole unit from coming and going at the same time, so your cousin may have served with the same Marines but their unit designation may have changed.<br><br>
If you can get me the units name, I might be able to also direct you toward where you might be able to get the actual combat report surrounding that action. It takes months to get that info but its possible.<br><br>
Cook
